all ranking of the institution as a whole by College Factual  Overall  College Factual ranked VMI s international relations department 18th in the nation in the category of international relations and national security  just behind Brown University and ahead of George Mason University  The College Factual rankings were recently reported in USA Today  Earlier this month  U S  News and World Report ranked the Institute fourth in the nation among public liberal arts colleges  behind the U S  Naval Academy  the U S  Military Academy  and the U S  Air Force Academy   VMI      VMI a  Best Value  VMI has been recognized for the value of its education    VMI File Photo by Kevin Remington  LEXINGTON  Va  Oct  7  2014   VMI continues to place highly among the nation s top colleges and universities in rankings released recently by several news outlets  Money magazine ranked VMI eighth in the category of best value liberal arts schools  behind Harvey Mudd College  Williams College  and Amherst College  The best value category calculates the average net price of a degree by taking a college s or university s sticker price and subtracting institutional aid  and then comparing it to the average salary of a graduate within five years  as reported by Payscale com  Liberal arts schools are classified as those that award more than half of their degrees in the liberal arts  Money magazine also ranked VMI 18th out of the 665 colleges and universities listed in a new national best colleges ranking  and fourth in the liberal arts category  higher than any other liberal arts college in the state  as previously reported  In addition to those rankings  VMI s Department of International Relations and Political Science has been named as one of the best values in the nation in the category of international relations and national security  as reported by College Factual  an independent college rankings organization  VMI was ranked eighth in that category  just behind Stanford University  To calc